To active the virtualenv:

* You need some basic system packages. Install them as 'root':

    aptitude install python python-pip libxml2-dev libxslt1-dev libsasl2-dev libldap2-dev

* Go to the main directory where is tryton, normaly one directory above it.

* If the enviroment is not created, do in the main directory:

    virtualenv --no-site-packages  .

* To active the environment:

    source bin/activate

* To install dependencies:

    pip install -r tryton-buildout/requirements.txt


More things to know:

* To see the libraries installed in the virtualenv:

    yolk -l

* If you neet to update the dependencies file:

    pip freeze > tryton-buildout/requirements.txt

    (And commit the changes)

* To logout the virtualnev:

    deactivate
